      "writtenOn": "2026-07-06T19:24:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The main concern I have with this is we\u0027re changing the existing behavior. Before, if one of these calls failed, we\u0027d get an unhandled exception and crash the service. Then we\u0027d try a few restarts of the service and Quiesce the BMC if it continued to fail. Now we\u0027ll just log an error to the journal and continue. That seems like undefined behavior. What if we log the error but still just throw the exception?",
      "revId": "3e083c31edddddff1a076fae782a94529eb341c6",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
