      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-08T05:36:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree the current try/catch changes the failure semantics. \n\nIf the goal is only to improve observability, the safer pattern is to log the exception and then rethrow it. That preserves the existing fail-fast behavior while still adding context to the journal. I’d recommend changing these handlers to catch (...) {log; throw;}\n\nlogging and then throw; is the correct approach",
      "parentUuid": "6daa98ef_2f1ee0d5",
      "revId": "3e083c31edddddff1a076fae782a94529eb341c6",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    }
